Donor 7042 has fathered 99 ‘Viking babies’ across the world through the clinic Nordic Cryobank Trust .
Ten of his offspring have already been diagnosed with NF1, a condition which can increase the risk of cancer, cause learning difficulties and reduce a sufferer’s lifespan by up to 15 years .
A child born from a parent with the defective gene has up to a 50% chance of developing the disease .